I tried a slightly different fix were we just check in the filter command whether there is more than 1 file OR if there is a single file but it is a partial scan, Scan Length < File sizeInBytes and that seems to work as well without building up the fileName set which may be an issue with very large numbers of files.

```java
private boolean isPartialFileScan(CombinedScanTask task) {
    if (task.files().size() == 1) {
      FileScanTask fileScanTask = task.files().iterator().next();
      boolean test = (fileScanTask.file().fileSizeInBytes() - fileScanTask.length()) != 0;
      return test;
    } else {
      return false;
    }
  }
```

